<br><table align=center border=0 width=70%><tr><td colspan=4 align=center><h3>General</h3></td></tr><tr><td class=eohead><b>Updated</b></td><td width=1% class=eohead></td><td width=19% nowrap class=eohead><b>Title</b></td><td nowrap class=eohead><b>Description</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class=even>12/15/03</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/Gem/Magelos/GraffeMagelo.jpg" TARGET="_blank">Graffe Magelo Background (No Portrait)</a></td><td class=even>This Magelo background has the window for the portrait removed as well as the spots for name and class on the bottom. To install it on your magelo set your background image to this under "Update character" and set background color to black.</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>12/15/03</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/Gem/Magelos/GraffePortrait.jpg" TARGET="_blank">Graffe Magelo Background</a></td><td class=odd>This is my Magelo background for Graffe's which includes the picture portrait and spots for name and class on the bottom. Use any graphic editor to add your own screenshot (322 width, 232 height).</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/eq-icons.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">EQ Icons</a></td><td class=even>Created and submitted by Luizito, these are icons based on some Everquest Spell Icons and the such to replace your computer's icons anywhere you wish to.</td></tr></td></tr></table>
<br><table align=center border=0 width=70%><tr><td colspan=4 align=center><h3>UI Mods</h3></td></tr><tr><td class=eohead><b>Updated</b></td><td width=1% class=eohead></td><td width=19% nowrap class=eohead><b>Title</b></td><td nowrap class=eohead><b>Description</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class=even>09/18/03</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/merloc_arcane_spellbook_1.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Tome of the Arcane</a></td><td class=even>Created by Merloc Kole, this is a mod to alter the way the spellbook looks. 
<li>No "Done" button, who needs it? 
<li>No left/right page turn buttons, simply click on the background of the page to turn. 
<li>A more compact layout, reducing the covered area from 498x395 to 371x315 pixels. 
<li>A better title! 
<li>Different background and text colors, (edit: spellbook01.tga to make your own background). </td></tr><tr><td class=odd>01/14/03</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="downloads/dynamite_player_window.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Dynamite Player Window</a></td><td class=odd>Created by Dynamite Shortfuze, Fennin Ro server, this is a mod for the player window. 
<li>Adds the Experience and Alternate Experience guages to the window. 
<li>Adds the player's AC and ATK numbers to the window. 
<li>Displays the percentages of each of the five guages. 
<li>Displays the player's current HP and maximum HP as numbers in the window. 
<li>Removed the surname from being displayed, shrunk the player's first name to occupy less space.</td></tr></td></tr></table>
<br><table align=center border=0 width=70%><tr><td colspan=4 align=center><h3>Programs</h3></td></tr><tr><td class=eohead><b>Updated</b></td><td width=1% class=eohead></td><td width=19% nowrap class=eohead><b>Title</b></td><td nowrap class=eohead><b>Description</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class=even>11/27/03</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="http://home.comcast.net/~jdscogin/eq.html" TARGET="_blank">LOY Research Utility</a></td><td class=even>For those who are making a living off their researching skills, they might want to take a look at this program created by Chantmon on Morell-Thule. Others like me who are working as guildmules for research components can use it as a nifty and quick tool when working with the spells/components.</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="/downloads/sneaky_amp?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Sneaky Amp</a></td><td class=odd>Control WinAmp from within Everquest. This is a download must for anybody that enjoys music.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="http://kaboom.shortweb.com/Applications/EQSR.html" TARGET="_blank">EQ Sound Ripper</a></td><td class=even>Created by Kaboom of the Saryn server, this neat little proggy will extract the bitmaps and the wav files from your Everquest directory. I've always extracted them the tedious way.. but now you can bet this is what I'll be using!</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Mana Calulator Executable</a></td><td class=odd>An executable program made for Windows that will calculate your current mana points. Fill in the blanks with your current information and have it calculate how much mana you have to spend. This program requires you to have the virtual basic dynamic link file msvbvm60.dll within your windows\system directory.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="http://www.eqcaster.com/" TARGET="_blank">EQ Caster</a></td><td class=even>A great utility to look at the spell data found within your Everquest directory (spdat.eff). The author keeps up on the program very steadily. Keep in mind when reading the data that some data is false. Verant doesn't put the exact info in the spdat.eff file and server side info is totally different. Do not trust all that you read. The link is just a link to the author's site because he always has new projects going on. Keep up the good work Vaslin!</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="downloads/EQmwdc3.5.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Mana / Weapon Damage Calc 3.5</a></td><td class=odd>Very well written executable for Mana Calculations with the added benefeit of calculating our melee damage! If you have any problems getting it to run, you may be needing system files.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">SFManaCalc</a></td><td class=even>This is a simple mana calculator which lets you calculate your mana, be it on an INT or WIS base calculation, without having to do anything special. The calculator will also display mana for every level from 1 to 50, and depending if your character is a pure caster, or a hybrid class, you will get the appropriate results. Thanks to Rindelk Darkcastyr of Fennnin Ro for creating this great little program.</td></tr></td></tr></table>
<br><table align=center border=0 width=70%><tr><td colspan=4 align=center><h3>Spreadsheets</h3></td></tr><tr><td class=eohead><b>Updated</b></td><td width=1% class=eohead></td><td width=19% nowrap class=eohead><b>Title</b></td><td nowrap class=eohead><b>Description</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/EQ_TradeSkills_and_Research.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">EQ Trade Skills & Research</a></td><td class=even>Created by Xekl Xephyre of Xegony, this spreadsheet is a download must. Simply loaded with all kinds of trade and research info as well as wizard spell damage info.</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="downloads/wizard.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Research Spreadsheet</a></td><td class=odd>Created by Boots at the Crossroads Gaming Network, this Microsoft Excel Spreadsheet will help you keep track of your runes and also tell you what spells you can create with the runes you have. Highly Recommended.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/practice.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Practice Spreadsheet</a></td><td class=even>Also created by Boots at the Crossroads Gaming Network, this Microsoft Exel Spreadsheet will help you keep track of your Practice components for research.</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="downloads/Wizstuff.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Item Bonus Calculator</a></td><td class=odd>This spreadsheet is in MS Excel 97/95 format. It is used to calculate item bonuses to stats, AC, mana, and HP. Very nice little spreadsheet. Thanks to Baks of Veeshan for creating this and sending it in.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/manaint.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Mana / Int Spreadsheet</a></td><td class=even>Itzokae Blastenburn of Cazic-Thule made an Excel spreadsheet which calculates the mana bonuses gained from intelligence bonuses by level and a chart which tells how much of an intelligence increase is needed to equal the mana bonus of an item by level. The latter chart makes it a bit easier to determine the point at which to switch from mana+ items to intelligence+ items.</td></tr><tr><td class=odd>05/20/02</td><td class=odd></td><td class=odd><a href="downloads/manadmg.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Mana / Damage Spreadsheet</a></td><td class=odd>This spreadsheet can make a comparison of mana available and damage possible with that mana, for two different Wizard's Intelligence. Changing cells B4 and D4, you can compare your abilities with your current and your intended ( or you friend's :) Intelligence. This spreadsheet requires you to have Microsoft Excel upon your system and an unzipping program such as WinZip to unpack it. Spreadsheet compiled by Nenad of Cazic Thule.</td></tr><tr><td class=even>05/20/02</td><td class=even></td><td class=even><a href="downloads/intreq.zip?PHPSESSID=0023b6d6bf1c84c76155c5bfcca5d393">Inventory INT / Mana Spreadsheet</a></td><td class=even>Simple Excel spreadsheet with a unique feature of allowing you to edit each slot for each item you may have (or not have) that adds to INT or mana. A good way to figure out what is the best combination of items once you hit 200 INT. Thanks to Zypher of Rodcet Nife for creating this.</td></tr></td></tr></table>
